Edge cases for kd
=================

	>>> import kd

More modules for testing
------------------------

	>>> import sys

Command lines
-------------

We allow more than two args on command line

	>>> sys.argv = ['kd.py', 'start', 'here', 'or', 'there']
	>>> kd.parse_command_line()
	('start', ['here', 'or', 'there'])

And no args at all

	>>> sys.argv = ['kd.py']
	>>> kd.parse_command_line()
	('', [])

find_directory()
----------------

Directories sought must be real

	>>> kd.find_directory('rubbish', [])
	Traceback (most recent call last):
	...
	ValueError: ...

	>>> import path_strings
	>>> a_known_directory = path_strings.environ.JAB
	>>> a_known_name = '.jab'

Can send a blank as the sub-dir

	>>> kd.find_directory(a_known_directory, []).name == a_known_name
	True

If sub-dir is not found, get nothing
	>>> kd.find_directory(a_known_directory, ['this_is_not_real']) is None
	True


When main() fails it prints out an error
	>>> import sys
	>>> sys.argv = [ 'kd', 'no_such_directory' ]
	>>> kd.main()
	Error 'no_such_directory' is not a directory
	1

